parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and lunging of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in motion or when the driver is attempting to stop.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward or backward without warning
often when the brake pedal is depressed or when the vehicle is in gear. The engine RPM may increase
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience stalling
loss of power
or hesitation when accelerating. The check engine light may illuminate
and the vehicle may enter fail-safe mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission or clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or experience unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience difficulty shifting gears
slipping or hesitation when accelerating
or loss of power. The transmission may fail to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge forward, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into gear
the transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle surges forward or backward
the vehicle loses power
the engine idles roughly
the transmission makes a loud clunk or buzzing noise
the vehicle accelerates without warning
the vehicle shakes violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the engine to stall, lose power, or surge forward, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine fails to respond to the accelerator pedal
the vehicle surges forward or backward
the engine idles roughly
the throttle body warning light illuminates
the vehicle enters engine failsafe mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the all-wheel drive (AWD) system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, stability, or control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The AWD warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses traction
the vehicle shakes violently
the ABS system fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the engine to stall, surge, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine hesitates or surges when accelerating
the car lunges forward or backward
the check engine light comes on
and the "Engine Failsafe Mode" warning appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle surges or lunges forward or backward
the check engine light comes on
and the "Transmission Failsafe Mode" warning appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The air conditioning does not cool
the engine overheats
and the check engine light comes on.
